article.description: Adrian Nelson had 13 points and 15 rebounds to lead Northern Kentucky to a 68-52 win over Illinois-Chicago on Friday night, using a 30-0 second-half run to take command.
article.headline: Nelson lifts Northern Kentucky over UIC 68-52
article.linkText: Nelson lifts Northern Kentucky over UIC 68-52
article.story: CHICAGO -- Adrian Nelson had 13 points and 15 rebounds to lead Northern Kentucky to a 68-52 win over Illinois-Chicago on Friday night, using a 30-0 second-half run to take command. Trailing 33-25, the Norse scored 30 consecutive points over a span of under 11 minutes to lead 59-33 with six minutes left. The Flames committed eight turnovers and missed 13 shots during their drought. Trevon Faulkner had 15 points for Northern Kentucky (11-6, 3-2 Horizon League). Jalen Tate added 12 points and six assists. Tyler Sharpe, whose 15 points per game heading into the matchup was second on the Norse, was held to seven points on 2-of-10 shooting. Michael Diggins had 15 points and nine rebounds for the Flames (6-12, 1-4), whose losing streak reached four games. Tarkus Ferguson added 12 points. Marcus Ottey had 11 points. Godwin Boahen scored five points despite heading into the contest as the Flames' second leading scorer at 11 points per game. He made 20% from 3-point range (1 of 5). Northern Kentucky faces IUPUI on the road on Sunday.
